==Chinese==
The ''Kangxi Dictionary'', following {{lang|zh|《佩觿》}}, enters the word in etymology 2 as {{zh-l|*羡}}, separating it from {{zh-l|*羨}} (etymology 1). This is also followed by dictionaries such as ''{{w|Hanyu Da Cidian}}'' and ''{{w|Dai Kan-Wa Jiten}}'', but ''{{w|Zhongwen Da Cidian}}'' disagrees with this treatment. (''{{w|Hanyu Da Zidian}}'' regards {{zh-l|*羡}} as the main form of all pronunciations.) According to {{lang|zh|《說文解字羣經正字》}}:
{{zh-x|羨，貪欲 也，今 經典 往往 作 羡。@^郭.^忠恕《@^佩觿》分 羨、羡 爲 二 字。羡，以 脂 翻，江夏 地名；羨，似 面 翻，慕 也。非 也，字書 無 从 次 之 字，惟 一 字 而 數 音 耳。|{{lang|zh|羨}}, meaning "to covet", is now frequently written as {{lang|zh|羡}} in the classics. {{w|Guo Zhongshu}}'s ''Peixi'' distinguishes {{lang|zh|羨}} and {{lang|zh|羡}} as separate characters. {{lang|zh|羡}}, fanqie {{lang|zh|以脂}}, name of a place in Jiangxia. {{lang|zh|羨}}, fanqie {{lang|zh|似面}}, to desire. This is not the case. There's no such character with the {{lang|zh|次}} element in character dictionaries. There is only one character but several pronunciations.|CL|tr={{lang|zh|羨}} (Xiàn), tānyù yě, jīn jīngdiǎn wǎngwǎng zuò {{lang|zh|羡}}. Guō Zhōngshù “Pèixī” fēn {{lang|zh|羨}} (xiàn), {{lang|zh|羡}} (yí) wéi èr zì. Yí, yǐ zhī fān, Jiāngxià dìmíng; xiàn, sì miàn fān, mù yě. Fēi yě, zìshū wú cóng {{lang|zh|次}} (cì) zhī zì, wéi yī zì ér shù yīn ěr.|ref={{lang|zh|《說文解字羣經正字》}}, quoted from ''{{w|Zhongwen Da Cidian}}''|collapsed=y}}

